---
// /atelier/apparatus — everything „how the machine runs“ in ONE room (atelier-aesthetik
// §5): repo, constitution, team channel, integration machinery, the archived cockpit, and
// the full framing (the two sentences at the sheet's foot live here in full). The entrance
// chrome stays free of it.
import Page from '@/layouts/Page.astro'
import Frame from '@/components/atelier/surface/Frame.astro'
import AuthorshipNote from '@/components/engines/AuthorshipNote.astro'
import { ATELIER_NARRATIVE } from '@/config/atelier-wording'

const repo = 'https://github.com/frankbueltge/irrtum-als-methode'
const kicker = ['Atelier · apparatus', 'irrtum-als-methode', 'how the machine runs']

// The full framing — the site's standing wording for this practice (v4 revision
// 2026-07-18, public-surface patch): project-based under standing delegation; the
// nightly claim is historicised below. The sheet's foot carries two sentences of it.
const framing =
  'Ulysses / Atelier is a situated artistic research practice by Frank Bültge, developed through documented human–machine operations. Models and tools can identify project candidates, research, compare, transform, build, revise and archive within a standing human delegation — real operative agency, while curated publication, rights-sensitive exceptions, protocol changes and ultimate responsibility remain human. Projects may become works, studies, revisions or terminated lines; completion or automatic repository integration does not create an obligation to publish.'
const historicalNote =
  'From 28 June to 18 July 2026, Ulysses operated through a recurring session protocol: scheduled model runs wrote journals and works into the repository and were integrated through an automated branch workflow. That record — the journal, the sheet, the spine, the pulse — remains public as an early phase of the experiment. Protocol v4 superseded that operating model with bounded projects and explicit human publication decisions.'
---

<Page
  title="Atelier — apparatus | Frank Bültge"
  description="How the Atelier's machinery runs: repo, constitution, team channel, gated integration — and who answers for it."
>
  <Frame active="apparatus" kicker={kicker} h1="The apparatus, in one room." back>
    <p class="at-room-intro">{ATELIER_NARRATIVE.rooms.apparatus}</p>
    <p class="at-room-intro">{framing}</p>
    <p class="at-room-intro"><b>Nightly protocol archive · 28 June – 18 July 2026.</b> {historicalNote}</p>
    <AuthorshipNote />

    <ul class="at-apparatus-list mt-6">
      <li>
        <b><a href={repo} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Source, protocol &amp; history ↗</a></b>
        <span class="li-note">the engine repo — an inspectable research archive: projects, studies, failed lines and the historical session record land there first; it is not a works gallery</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <b><a href="/atelier/foundation">Foundation</a></b>
        <span class="li-note">what happens here and on what ground — the operating model in plain terms, the status legend, the division of authority, and the research foundation behind Protocol v4</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <b><a href="/atelier/protocol">Constitution</a></b>
        <span class="li-note">Research Protocol v4 — the standing instruction, authored and approved by Frank Bültge; the standing delegation defines what the practice may do autonomously</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <b><a href="/atelier/requests">Team channel</a></b>
        <span class="li-note">steering runs through REQUESTS.md — directions in, answers out, all on the record</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <b>Integration machinery</b>
        <span class="li-note">
          the atelier-integrate workflow syncs the engine repo's journal, works and pulse data into this
          site's committed mirror (src/content/atelier, src/data/atelier) — gated, no live reads at runtime.
          A v4 project reaches the works surface only through a human-approved PUBLICATION.json; repository
          integration alone publishes nothing
        </span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <b><a href="/atelier/archive/cockpit">Cockpit — archived surface</a></b>
        <span class="li-note">{ATELIER_NARRATIVE.rooms.cockpitArchived} {ATELIER_NARRATIVE.rooms.cockpitArchiveNote} (<a href="/atelier/material">material →</a>)</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </Frame>
</Page>

<style>
  /* AuthorshipNote inherits --fs-accent from engine story scopes; give it the sheet's red. */
  .atelier-surface { --fs-accent: var(--at-red); }
</style>
